{
  "page": "Roger Reyne",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Reyne\" title=\"House Reyne\"><img alt=\"House Reyne.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/3c/House_Reyne.svg/50px-House_Reyne.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/3c/House_Reyne.svg/75px-House_Reyne.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/3c/House_Reyne.svg/100px-House_Reyne.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Lord</span><br />Roger Reyne<br /><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> the Red Lion</span></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Reyne\" title=\"House Reyne\"><img alt=\"House Reyne.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/3c/House_Reyne.svg/50px-House_Reyne.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/3c/House_Reyne.svg/75px-House_Reyne.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/3c/House_Reyne.svg/100px-House_Reyne.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Roger_Reyne.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Roger Reyne.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/07/Roger_Reyne.jpg/350px-Roger_Reyne.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"465\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/07/Roger_Reyne.jpg/525px-Roger_Reyne.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/07/Roger_Reyne.jpg/700px-Roger_Reyne.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Art by iamagri ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nThe Red Lion<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Castamere\" title=\"Lord of Castamere\">Lord of Castamere</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Reyne\" title=\"House Reyne\">House Reyne</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">Westermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nor before <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_218_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">218&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/261_AC\" title=\"261 AC\">261&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Castamere\" title=\"Castamere\">Castamere</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Reyne\" title=\"Robert Reyne\">Robert Reyne</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)<i></i></li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Roger Reyne</b>, known as <b>the Red Lion</b>, was a <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Castamere\" title=\"Lord of Castamere\">Lord of Castamere</a> and head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Reyne\" title=\"House Reyne\">House Reyne</a>. He was a famous <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a>, and considered one of the deadliest men of the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Peake_Uprising\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Peake Uprising</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Reynes_and_Tarbecks\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Reynes and Tarbecks</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Rebellion\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Rebellion</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Roger_Reyne&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Peake_Uprising\">Peake Uprising</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Roger_Reyne&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Peake Uprising\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Roger became Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Castamere\" title=\"Castamere\">Castamere</a> after the death of his father <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Reyne\" title=\"Robert Reyne\">Robert</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Peake_Uprising\" title=\"Peake Uprising\">Peake Uprising</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/233_AC\" title=\"233 AC\">233&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> According to a semi-canon source, Roger executed seven captive <a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\">Peakes</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Storming_of_Starpike\" title=\"Storming of Starpike\">Starpike</a> before being halted by Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reynes_and_Tarbecks\">Reynes and Tarbecks</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Roger_Reyne&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Reynes and Tarbecks\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Roger and his younger brother, the cunning <a href=\"/index.php/Reynard_Reyne\" title=\"Reynard Reyne\">Reynard</a>, were often at <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a> once their sister <a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Reyne\" title=\"Ellyn Reyne\">Ellyn</a> married <a href=\"/index.php/Tion_Lannister\" title=\"Tion Lannister\">Tion Lannister</a>, the son of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_Lannister\" title=\"Gerold Lannister\">Gerold Lannister</a> and heir to the Rock. The brothers returned to <a href=\"/index.php/Castamere\" title=\"Castamere\">Castamere</a> after Tion's death, however, as Gerold began to groom <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos Lannister</a> for leadership. Ellyn was later rewed to <a href=\"/index.php/Walderan_Tarbeck\" title=\"Walderan Tarbeck\">Walderan Tarbeck</a>, Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Tarbeck_Hall\" title=\"Tarbeck Hall\">Tarbeck Hall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ca. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_255_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">255&#160;AC</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarbeck\" title=\"House Tarbeck\">House Tarbeck</a> angered King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon V Targaryen</a> through their territorial demands, according to a semi-canon source.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Lord Tytos sent Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Denys_Marbrand\" title=\"Denys Marbrand\">Denys Marbrand</a> to capture the Tarbecks, but Roger came to his sister's aid and his soldiers slew the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Marbrand\" title=\"House Marbrand\">Marbrand</a> men in the night before they reached Tarbeck Hall. Reynard convinced Tytos that the attack was a misunderstanding, claiming that Roger was unaware of Denys's identity and thought he was attacking <a href=\"/index.php/Outlaw\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Outlaw\">outlaws</a>. After Reynard offered apologies and a <a href=\"/index.php/Blood_price\" title=\"Blood price\">blood price</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Marbrand\" title=\"House Marbrand\">House Marbrand</a>, Tytos pardoned Roger Reyne, and Lord and Lady Tarbeck as well.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Roger and his sister were present at the feast in the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a> where the betrothal of <a href=\"/index.php/Genna_Lannister\" title=\"Genna Lannister\">Genna Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Emmon_Frey\" title=\"Emmon Frey\">Emmon Frey</a> was announced. While Ellyn laughed, the Red Lion left the hall in anger.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Roger capably led <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a>'s army in the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Ninepenny_Kings\" title=\"War of the Ninepenny Kings\">War of the Ninepenny Kings</a> after the death of <a href=\"/index.php/Jason_Lannister_(son_of_Gerold)\" title=\"Jason Lannister (son of Gerold)\">Jason Lannister</a>. Roger <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knighted</a> his squire, Tytos's second son <a href=\"/index.php/Kevan_Lannister\" title=\"Kevan Lannister\">Kevan</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Rebellion\">Rebellion</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Roger_Reyne&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Rebellion\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:TheProudLordReyne_by_fuderiki.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fc/TheProudLordReyne_by_fuderiki.jpg/300px-TheProudLordReyne_by_fuderiki.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fc/TheProudLordReyne_by_fuderiki.jpg/450px-TheProudLordReyne_by_fuderiki.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fc/TheProudLordReyne_by_fuderiki.jpg/600px-TheProudLordReyne_by_fuderiki.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:TheProudLordReyne_by_fuderiki.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Red Lion of Castamere, drowned within his own seat</div></div></div>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/261_AC\" title=\"261 AC\">261&#160;AC</a> after the war, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>, the eldest son and heir of Lord Tytos, desired to reaffirm <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a>'s control over the west. The Reynes and Tarbecks <a href=\"/index.php/Reyne-Tarbeck_rebellion\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Reyne-Tarbeck rebellion\">rose in rebellion</a> against their liege lord, Tytos. Roger's host arrived too late to prevent Tywin from exterminating the Tarbecks at Tarbeck Hall,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and the outnumbered Reynes failed to defeat Tywin in a surprise charge. Roger became feverish from a crossbow bolt and Reynard led the surviving Reynes back to <a href=\"/index.php/Castamere\" title=\"Castamere\">Castamere</a>, where they took refuge in its mines.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>According to a semi-canon source, Tywin declined Reynard's terms and Roger's offer of single combat.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Instead, the Lannisters diverted a nearby stream into Castamere, drowning all within.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> A song known as \"<a href=\"/index.php/The_Rains_of_Castamere\" title=\"The Rains of Castamere\">The Rains of Castamere</a>\" was composed as a commemoration of the event.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Roger_Reyne&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Reyne\" title=\"Robert Reyne\">Robert</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\